<br>
An NSWR using 95 percent uranium has a calculated Isp of around 480,000, with an exhaust velocity calculated to be 4,700 km/sec.<br>
<br>
It also can generate 3,000,000 pounds of thrust, so a surface launch is possible, although VERY dirty.  Likewise, it could land on any body in the Solar System with a surface.  (Jupiter is right out.)<br>
<br>
So, using the old 40 percent rule of thumb, and assuming the ship has a launch mass of 1400 tons, you have 560 tons of high-octane uranium fuel, use another 420 tons for vessel structure, and have 420 tons for pure payload.  This would have a total DeltaV of 2350 Km/sec, EASILY enough to get to Mars and still do your little tour of the planets, no matter WHERE they are.<br>
<br>
So, it is possible, but it takes Isp in the hundreds of thousands to do it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
